raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "django-denied" %}
{% set version = "1.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/django-denied-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 130da88b74984c36fd8deef44e5cec7b759828c514f1fffcb541a12b1c9f96fa

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 1

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}
    - setuptools
  run:
    - django >=3.2
    - python >={{ python_min }}

test:
  imports:
    - denied
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}

about:
  home: https://github.com/mblayman/django-denied
  summary: An authorization system based exclusively on allow lists
  license: MIT
  license_file:
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - thewchan
